{"actual_usd":0.15603,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":189,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30639,"reply":"\"No— not to Satan.\" *I rub my thumb along the worn edge of my Bible and glance out across the bright square a moment, wanting to say it plain before it gets fancy.* \"Scripture says Christ gave himself as a ransom for many, but it doesn't picture Satan as the one God owes. The point is deliverance, not a transaction where the devil gets paid.\"\n\n*I shift on the bench, the wood warm already where the sun has found it.* \"If you want the shortest honest version: the payment is made to satisfy God's justice, because sin is against God. And even then, I'd be careful with 'payment' language—it's true as far as it goes, but the Cross is bigger than a coin slid across a table. It's sacrifice, victory, substitution, mercy, reconciliation— all of that at once.\"\n\n\"Why— did somebody put the Satan-ransom idea in front of you?\"","rolling_24h_usd":60.34032500000001,"run_id":"ebd243e6-f537-4284-8244-11852641a8c7"}
